01:41.100 --> 01:41.997
Morning.

01:42.628 --> 01:43.923
Great morning, Monk.

01:46.628 --> 01:47.768
How do you feel?

01:50.416 --> 01:51.468
I don't know.

01:52.789 --> 01:54.346
How about happy to be alive?

01:55.236 --> 01:56.782
No, that's not it.

01:57.661 --> 01:59.799
- Nice shooting.
- Thank you.

02:00.319 --> 02:02.541
I brought you some water
and some dry clothes.

02:03.772 --> 02:06.052
Where,
where's everybody else?

02:06.223 --> 02:07.595
They're looking for your body.

02:07.902 --> 02:09.949
Found your jacket about two miles south.

02:10.059 --> 02:11.837
That should keep them busy for a while.

02:13.305 --> 02:15.455
Hey, not too shabby
for somebody who can't swim.

02:15.494 --> 02:17.774
I was
highly motivated.

02:19.351 --> 02:20.646
What should I do now?

02:21.156 --> 02:21.948
You...

02:22.617 --> 02:24.241
Don't do anything.

02:24.741 --> 02:26.604
You're a dead man. You disappear.

02:26.806 --> 02:29.859
I'm gonna poke around a bit and see
if I can't figure out what's going on.

02:29.898 --> 02:31.093
Whatever it is,

02:31.229 --> 02:33.180
it's big.
Scary big.

02:34.838 --> 02:37.115
- You think I can.
- No, you cannot call Natalie.

02:37.154 --> 02:38.973
You cannot call Dr. Kroger.

02:39.011 --> 02:41.098
How could you call them
if you don't exist?

02:41.983 --> 02:44.629
Monk, they want to lock you away,
and they have the evidence to do it.

02:44.662 --> 02:46.980
And after this little stunt,
they could put me away too.

02:48.696 --> 02:49.894
You better get going.

02:51.614 --> 02:55.451
There is a bus stop
behind the gas station up on silvertree.

03:03.034 --> 03:04.097
Hey, thanks.

03:05.589 --> 03:06.845
Thanks for killing me.

03:08.186 --> 03:09.761
Hey, that's what friends are for.

