04:26.985 --> 04:27.862
Natalie.

04:29.220 --> 04:29.858
Hey.

04:31.400 --> 04:32.501
How are you doing?

04:32.590 --> 04:34.029
I don't know. About the same.

04:35.020 --> 04:35.928
These were

04:36.685 --> 04:37.803
out front.

04:38.755 --> 04:39.702
From Sharona.

04:41.076 --> 04:42.139
They're beautiful.

04:44.728 --> 04:46.216
Why don't you put them over there.

04:50.201 --> 04:52.868
She and Benjy are gonna
fly in for the service.

04:53.632 --> 04:54.632
It's funny.

04:54.896 --> 04:57.427
When he was alive, he always said
he didn't have any friends.

05:02.035 --> 05:04.779
Hey, would it be okay
if I wrote a song for the service?

05:05.054 --> 05:07.430
Yeah, Randy, that would be wonderful.

05:08.163 --> 05:09.400
He would've liked that.

05:09.473 --> 05:11.522
Mr. Monk was a big, big, big.

05:13.535 --> 05:15.642
He knew how much you really love music.

05:17.690 --> 05:18.560
Great.

05:19.881 --> 05:20.665
Look,

05:21.314 --> 05:22.763
I found one of him smiling.

05:23.552 --> 05:25.233
Didn't see that very often.

05:28.590 --> 05:30.630
Listen, Natalie,
the Captain's out front.

05:30.727 --> 05:32.137
He'd really like to come in.

05:34.050 --> 05:34.649
No.

05:38.004 --> 05:40.845
Natalie, he
didn't have a choice.

05:41.113 --> 05:43.083
- Monk fired the first shot.
- Don't tell me that.

05:43.103 --> 05:44.301
There's always a choice.

05:44.337 --> 05:46.617
- He could have fired a warning shot.
- That's not trained.

05:46.656 --> 05:49.438
You know what? How about shot him
in the leg or not fired at all?

05:51.887 --> 05:52.660
God,

05:53.765 --> 05:54.809
I can't believe it.

05:55.844 --> 05:57.873
- I'm sorry.
- I can't believe he's gone.

05:59.692 --> 06:00.723
I'm so sorry.

06:03.208 --> 06:04.638
Hey, the door was open.

06:09.696 --> 06:11.106
Is there anything i can do?

06:16.541 --> 06:18.621
I understand.
I'll catch you later.

06:19.460 --> 06:20.948
Wait, no, Captain.

06:22.285 --> 06:23.154
I'm sorry.

06:23.913 --> 06:25.884
This must be harder on you than anybody.

06:26.392 --> 06:27.803
Please, come, come in.

06:29.101 --> 06:29.958
Thanks.

06:31.136 --> 06:32.605
Pretty flowers.

06:34.834 --> 06:37.636
- So have they found his.
- No,

06:38.529 --> 06:39.495
not yet.

06:39.631 --> 06:41.740
The coast guard says
they might never find him.

06:41.824 --> 06:43.254
It just depends on the currents.

06:43.447 --> 06:44.133
Yep.

06:44.197 --> 06:46.298
It's just that i'm planning the service,

06:46.713 --> 06:48.287
and it's just hard without closure.

06:48.365 --> 06:49.877
I appreciate that.

06:50.738 --> 06:51.472
I...

06:53.375 --> 06:55.945
Randy told me that you rented out
the legion of honor.

06:56.333 --> 06:57.009
Yeah.

06:57.624 --> 07:00.608
And he also said that you took out
a loan to cover the costs?

07:00.822 --> 07:02.696
- Yeah, that's right.
- It's just...

07:03.489 --> 07:05.595
I don't think you need
to be so extravagant.

07:07.863 --> 07:09.544
- You don't?
- No.

07:09.933 --> 07:11.930
In fact, i remember once, Monk told me,

07:11.976 --> 07:14.690
he said that if anything ever happened
to him, he...

07:16.149 --> 07:18.009
Wouldn't want anybody to go into debt.

07:18.068 --> 07:20.004
I cannot believe you're saying that.

07:20.100 --> 07:21.452
He was your friend.

07:21.760 --> 07:25.617
- Nat, i'm just trying to honor what he.
- No, no, no, no, no. He loved you.

07:25.637 --> 07:27.918
I mean, he really loved you,
and you sit here

07:28.401 --> 07:30.488
I changed my mind.
I want you out of here.

07:30.623 --> 07:32.208
I'm going to ask you to leave,

07:33.560 --> 07:34.449
please.

07:35.248 --> 07:36.060
Look,

07:37.103 --> 07:39.109
- Natalie, you don't understand.
- Yeah, I don't.

07:39.129 --> 07:40.710
I'm sorry, Captain. Good-bye.

08:01.677 --> 08:05.039
<i>WELCOME TO SPARKS NEVADA</i>

08:22.934 --> 08:24.074
Cual es el problema?

08:24.112 --> 08:27.417
-<i> Apurate!</i>
-  <i>Apurate! Ombré.</i>

08:28.991 --> 08:31.630
- What's the problem?
- Es el nuevo. Es terrible!

08:31.734 --> 08:33.856
Rodriguez, how many times
have I told you?

08:33.876 --> 08:35.789
It doesn't have to be perfect, hombre.

08:36.001 --> 08:38.842
You don't have to clean
the inside of a cigarette lighter.

08:38.900 --> 08:42.129
Nobody cares about the inside
of a damn cigarette lighter!

08:43.477 --> 08:44.559
Put it down!

08:45.616 --> 08:46.474
Rodriguez,

08:46.571 --> 08:48.656
the faster we work,
the more money we make.

08:49.126 --> 08:51.870
Fast, more money.
Slow, less money.

08:52.212 --> 08:53.449
Comprende?
Good.

08:59.226 --> 09:00.753
55, you're all set!

09:03.089 --> 09:04.352
Look, Rodriguez,

09:04.680 --> 09:05.946
it's not that complicated.

09:06.018 --> 09:07.525
Even you can understand.

09:07.662 --> 09:08.687
We get paid

09:09.138 --> 09:10.008
per car,

09:10.234 --> 09:11.793
- get it?
- Per car.

09:13.650 --> 09:15.737
Mr. Larry!
Larry, relax.

09:15.939 --> 09:17.479
You're going to have another stroke.

09:17.638 --> 09:20.440
This guy's the best rag man i ever seen.

09:20.498 --> 09:23.009
Look at that car. It's better
than new. It's like a diamond.

09:23.029 --> 09:24.739
When the owner sees it,
he gonna love it.

09:24.759 --> 09:27.276
He gonna tell all his friends.
He's gonna be a customer for life.

09:27.332 --> 09:29.554
Well, it's about friggin' time.

09:29.713 --> 09:31.549
I've been waiting over there 20 minutes.

09:31.767 --> 09:33.255
You won't be seeing me again.

09:40.145 --> 09:41.208
Have a nice day.

09:43.024 --> 09:43.903
Rodriguez,

09:44.550 --> 09:45.768
i'm warning you.

09:47.535 --> 09:48.559
I'm warning you!

10:04.429 --> 10:06.013
Hello. One minute.

10:06.128 --> 10:07.253
Mr. Rodriguez?

10:07.314 --> 10:08.628
Just, just a minute.

10:12.241 --> 10:12.927
Hello.

10:12.947 --> 10:15.523
I'm sorry to bother you.
You were asking about room number ten.

10:15.562 --> 10:17.534
- You wanted to switch?
- Yeah.

10:20.427 --> 10:23.666
My father said ten will be available
on sunday, but

10:23.773 --> 10:26.037
you understand it's basically

10:26.080 --> 10:28.739
the same room, just
a different number.

10:32.912 --> 10:34.670
Right, I, I, I understand.

10:35.876 --> 10:38.949
Be a good girl.
I'm sorry, she's just a Puppy.

10:38.997 --> 10:40.369
We're still teaching her.

10:40.401 --> 10:43.121
She's not on a leash? Where's her leash?
She should have a leash.

10:43.141 --> 10:45.760
No. She has a special collar,
actually, a shock collar.

10:46.514 --> 10:48.698
My father put a wire around the motel.

10:48.947 --> 10:50.319
It's like an invisible fence.

10:50.490 --> 10:52.654
If she wanders too far,
she gets a little zap.

10:52.852 --> 10:54.861
Yeah, I know how she feels.

10:57.390 --> 10:58.162
Here.

10:58.226 --> 10:59.266
What's all this?

10:59.316 --> 11:01.613
It's just research.
I'm writing a story.

11:02.004 --> 11:04.282
You write about criminals?
Like, mysteries?

11:04.517 --> 11:06.631
- Well...
- You know what you should write about?

11:06.697 --> 11:08.115
You should write about this.

11:09.867 --> 11:12.319
It actually just happened
two miles from here.

11:12.377 --> 11:14.245
A highway worker was killed.

11:14.265 --> 11:16.643
- Really? Yeah?
- Yeah, it's a real-life mystery

11:16.693 --> 11:18.448
with real clues and everything.

11:19.562 --> 11:22.394
Yeah, it was hit-and-run, actually.
They're looking for a silver suv.

11:22.471 --> 11:24.281
- Yeah.
- I can leave it if you want.

11:24.339 --> 11:27.921
No, no, that, that's okay.
You, you can take it. Take, take...

11:29.104 --> 11:31.699
Well,
i'll let you get back to your work.

11:32.154 --> 11:34.197
- Good night, mr. Rodriguez.
- Good night.

11:34.673 --> 11:36.296
Eureka, what are you doing?

11:36.480 --> 11:38.393
Come on, Eureka,
let's go.

11:42.462 --> 11:43.738
Eureka.

11:46.430 --> 11:48.575
He's over here.
I think it might be your boy.

11:48.652 --> 11:50.768
Male caucasian, late 40s, 5'11".

11:51.069 --> 11:54.084
I read the posting.
Said gunshot wound.

11:54.142 --> 11:55.944
Yes, sir, it looks
like two to the chest.

11:55.982 --> 11:58.243
The coast guard just
fished him out of avalon bay.

12:00.828 --> 12:01.853
Is that a tattoo?

12:03.323 --> 12:04.193
Yes, sir.

12:21.619 --> 12:22.747
It's not him.

12:22.824 --> 12:24.578
<i>Of course it isn't him.</i>

12:24.673 --> 12:27.378
<i>I've been telling you, Monk is alive.</i>

12:27.512 --> 12:28.807
You can't be sure.

12:28.967 --> 12:31.827
<i>That's true, I can't. You can.</i>

12:32.427 --> 12:34.552
<i>He's out there. He's somewhere.</i>

12:35.182 --> 12:36.149
Find him!

12:43.018 --> 12:44.728
Does everybody have them?
You have yours?

12:44.758 --> 12:45.618
Good.

12:50.651 --> 12:51.578
Hey, captain.

12:52.335 --> 12:53.231
Are you okay?

12:53.518 --> 12:56.020
Yeah, i'm fine. Why wouldn't I be fine?

12:56.297 --> 12:58.771
No reason.
Rollins is still in the office.

12:59.116 --> 13:00.662
The guys are wearing these for Monk.

13:00.725 --> 13:02.492
We weren't sure
if you wanted to wear it.

13:02.581 --> 13:04.127
Of course I do, randy.

13:06.500 --> 13:07.640
Thank you.

13:09.152 --> 13:10.552
- Two?
- For the other arm.

13:11.863 --> 13:13.680
- Right. To make it even.
- Make 'em even.

13:13.741 --> 13:14.504
Monk.

13:18.876 --> 13:20.824
Hello, Sheriff Rollins.

13:21.560 --> 13:22.824
Make yourself at home.

13:23.201 --> 13:24.612
You read the paper today?

13:25.078 --> 13:25.818
I did.

13:25.902 --> 13:28.511
I read the sports page.
I did the jumble.

13:29.205 --> 13:30.466
Not the jumble.

13:30.563 --> 13:32.489
This,
page five.

13:34.975 --> 13:36.992
Male,
caucasian,

13:37.458 --> 13:38.560
5'11".

13:38.895 --> 13:39.939
Late 40s.

13:40.765 --> 13:42.209
- Is it Monk?
- No.

13:42.422 --> 13:43.437
It's not Monk.

13:44.215 --> 13:46.360
I was at the morgue last night.

13:46.857 --> 13:49.079
The guy had a tattoo and red hair.

13:50.159 --> 13:52.517
I thought it was strange.

13:52.800 --> 13:55.070
- What was strange?
- Well,

13:55.660 --> 13:57.650
i'll tell you what was strange.

14:02.057 --> 14:03.707
You weren't there.

14:05.103 --> 14:08.697
A bulletin was sent in. It was in
the daily log. You must have read it.

14:09.434 --> 14:12.338
You guys won't mind
if I hang around a few more days,

14:12.490 --> 14:14.808
see if anything else washes up?

14:16.015 --> 14:18.582
Knock yourself out.
We can use all the help we can get.

14:18.639 --> 14:20.803
- We all got to suffer.
- Yeah.

14:22.711 --> 14:25.308
- I'll see you boys around the Campus.
- Bye-bye.

14:36.366 --> 14:37.119
What?

14:38.081 --> 14:39.651
It's a good question.

14:40.462 --> 14:42.915
- Why didn't you check it out?
- Because I was busy.

14:43.108 --> 14:44.944
I was turning over rocks,

14:45.822 --> 14:48.160
trying to get a bead
on that son of a bitch.

14:54.058 --> 14:55.866
He just bought
a second house in Catalina.

14:55.905 --> 14:58.465
And a new BMW, and look at this.

15:00.065 --> 15:02.190
He's got two offshore bank accounts

15:02.812 --> 15:04.609
on a Sheriff's salary.

15:05.403 --> 15:07.993
Randy, this guy is dirty.
I can smell him.

15:30.095 --> 15:31.873
What is it?
This one's been repainted.

15:32.490 --> 15:33.669
Recently.

15:35.487 --> 15:36.879
It useto be silver.

15:38.663 --> 15:40.151
They're looking for a silver suv.

15:55.193 --> 15:56.193
Are you okay?

16:05.980 --> 16:07.139
What are you doing?

16:09.759 --> 16:11.904
Well, at least make it look
like you're working.

16:12.161 --> 16:13.896
I need you to look under the car.

16:14.244 --> 16:14.987
What?

16:15.045 --> 16:17.158
Just, behind this fender.

16:17.912 --> 16:19.555
Inside, tell me what you see.

16:20.191 --> 16:22.639
Check the axle.
You're gonna get us both fired.

16:22.736 --> 16:24.553
Right, right behind this front wheel.

16:27.379 --> 16:28.642
What are these?

16:37.003 --> 16:38.367
A highway worker was killed.

16:47.542 --> 16:51.922
And so these are gonna go to his
brother Ambrose's house, and

16:52.724 --> 16:54.579
those will go to my garage.

16:54.750 --> 16:56.821
All these books.
What was he, a professor?

16:57.843 --> 16:58.925
No, a Detective.

16:59.818 --> 17:01.905
An amazing Detective.

17:02.376 --> 17:04.387
He could look at a room or a person

17:04.425 --> 17:06.349
and see things that
nobody else could see.

17:06.521 --> 17:08.009
Like the car wash guy.

17:08.448 --> 17:09.267
Yeah.

17:10.156 --> 17:11.760
What car wash guy?

17:11.819 --> 17:13.798
The guy in Nevada.
I was just reading about him.

17:16.147 --> 17:18.002
Here.
It's in today's paper.

17:18.546 --> 17:20.150
They call him the "car wash Columbo."

17:20.632 --> 17:22.738
He solved a big hit-and-run case
single-handedly.

17:23.287 --> 17:24.968
Yeah. Sounds like a real character.

17:25.413 --> 17:27.925
His boss says it takes him a whole hour
to wipe down every car.

17:27.983 --> 17:29.510
Won't even use the same rag twice.

17:31.027 --> 17:32.031
Can I see that?

17:33.573 --> 17:34.384
Yeah.

17:36.663 --> 17:37.803
There's no picture.

17:37.947 --> 17:39.222
I guess he's modest too.

17:41.001 --> 17:42.721
Leland Rodriguez.

17:43.582 --> 17:45.328
His name is Leland?

17:48.756 --> 17:50.476
Captain Stottlemeyer. Where is he?

17:50.691 --> 17:52.140
- I don't know.
- Where is he?

17:54.025 --> 17:54.994
It's not mine.

17:55.083 --> 17:58.305
It matches the set in your mother's
kitchen. How do you explain that?

17:58.325 --> 17:59.581
My mom's not the only one.

17:59.627 --> 18:01.476
- I have to talk to you.
- what are you doing?

18:01.520 --> 18:04.504
Is this him? It's him, isn't it?
He's the "car wash Columbo."

18:05.361 --> 18:07.865
<i>CAR WASH COLUMBO</i>

18:09.103 --> 18:13.078
- Reginald, we need to take a break.
- Cool, i'll wait outside.

18:13.136 --> 18:14.144
Nice try, kid.

18:14.417 --> 18:16.954
Jackson, could you baby-sit
my young friend here for a minute?

18:26.508 --> 18:28.015
It's him, isn't it?

18:31.884 --> 18:32.947
Oh, my god.

18:34.526 --> 18:35.859
Oh, my god.

18:36.888 --> 18:37.970
Oh, my god.

18:38.897 --> 18:41.814
- Why didn't you tell me?
- Natalie, Natalie, Natalie, Natalie.

18:43.829 --> 18:45.259
I am so sorry.

18:45.414 --> 18:46.689
You're sorry?!

18:48.180 --> 18:49.069
But how?

18:49.230 --> 18:51.900
Bulletproof vest.
We couldn't tell anybody.

18:54.203 --> 18:55.517
"Leland rodriguez"?

18:55.611 --> 18:57.663
- That's his name.
- Well, that's just stupid.

18:57.683 --> 18:58.947
What's he doing in Nevada?

18:58.986 --> 19:01.698
He's supposed to be avoiding attention,
staying off the radar.

19:01.718 --> 19:02.800
He's all alone?

19:02.836 --> 19:04.641
